    "analysis": "We identified intermittent short-lived metric anomalies across many services during the incident window, with the most prominent faults being 2-minute consecutive runs in recommendationservice (cpu, latency-50/90, mem) and frontend (cpu, latency-50/90) beginning around 2024-01-18 01:54:00 UTC. adservice had a large single-minute diskio spike (~2.14x P95) at ~01:54 but no sustained run. Because multiple service-level components show faults, we must use traces to determine which faulty service is the most downstream faulty component in the call chain (per the rules) and therefore the likely root cause service. The next step is to analyze trace telemetry for anomalies during the incident window, focusing on traces involving recommendationservice and frontend (and nearby downstream services such as productcatalogservice, checkoutservice, paymentservice) to see which faulty service appears downstream in anomalous traces and which has anomalous trace durations or error rates coincident with metric faults.",
