    "analysis": "From the trace analysis we observed two complementary signals: (1) checkoutservice and frontend traces show the largest number of anomalous samples across the window (many samples > global P95 beginning ~01:42–01:45 UTC), indicating widespread latency/backpressure in the request path; (2) recommendationservice traces show the most severe, concentrated latency spikes around ~01:54 UTC (very large breach ratios on duration_mean and duration_p95, and elevated trace durations to/from recommendationservice). Metric analysis earlier highlighted 2-minute consecutive anomaly runs in recommendationservice (cpu and latency) starting ~01:54 UTC and similar but milder runs in frontend around 01:54–02:00 UTC. Taken together, this points to recommendationservice experiencing a high-severity latency/CPU-related fault at ~01:54 UTC that propagates upstream (affecting frontend/checkout traces). To confirm the root-cause component and reason, we need to check logs (log aggregates and error logs) for recommendationservice and for frontend/checkout around the relevant timestamps to see if logs indicate errors, timeouts, or resource exhaustion.",
